reasoning: Extremely rare variant of GBS with estimated incidence 0.1-0.3 per 100k globally. Mid-range estimate 0.2 per 100k. High geographic variation: 1-7% of GBS cases in Western countries, 15-25% in Asian countries. Limited epidemiological data due to rarity.
source: Miller Fisher syndrome: an updated narrative review; PMC10484709 and Orphanet rare disease database.
